STEP 1: Compare the difference in price between the On-Demand v/s Spot pricing 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What to do : 
1.Open the Ec2 Dashboard 
2.Click on Instances
3.Click on Launch instances
4.Here choose the type of the instance you want to launch and See the cost of it 
  For the spot instnaces go the spot instacne section 

See the price diffecrence

Step 2: Update the Launch Template to support Spot 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Go to the  Old template used in the ASG 
Click on the modify button which will create a new version 
Go to the Additional setion 
In the purchase option : 
  *Do not do anything leave the options alone 
5.Do not change anything 
6.Click Create template version 

Step 3: Update the Auto Scaling Group to use Spot(Correct way)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What to do :
1.Go to the Ec2 -> Auto scaling group section 
2.Select the ASG
3.Click on Edit 
4.Under Launch template:
  *Select the new version you just created
5.The give other configuration and save it
6.Configure the instance type 
  *Choose the override the launch template option
  *Then select the multiple instace type as possible  or needed

Enable Mixed Instance / Spot 
One you have selected the mixed instance types : 
1.Scroll to instance purchase option's (in the ASG wizard )
2.Enable the Use of the mixed purchase option 
3.Configure:
The type and the amount of it needed
Instance purchase options Info

Instances distribution
To run fault-tolerant workloads at low cost, define a percentage of instances that will be Spot Instances. Spot Instances are spare EC2 capacity that offer steep discounts compared to On-Demand prices that AWS can interrupt with a 2-minute notification.
>> 1
% On-Demand
>> 99% Spot
Include On-Demand base capacity
Specify how much On-Demand capacity the Auto Scaling group should have for its base portion before scaling by percentages. The maximum group size will be increased (but not decreased) to this value.
>> 0
On-Demand Instances

Spot allocaiton strategy = lowest price

5.Complete  othere settings like:

Minimum, maximum, desired capacity → your choice
Availability zones → select one or more
Load balancer / Target group → attach if needed
Health checks → EC2 + ELB (recommended)
Tags → optional

Step 4: Launch the ASG
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
*Review and Create 
*Now the ASG will 
Launch 1 On-Demand t2.micro
Fill remaining capacity with Spot instances, picking from t2.micro, t3.micro, t3a.micro depending on price and availability

✅ Now Spot fallback works, and you can see all the options in the wizard

This is the way to use the spot instances in the Auto Scaling group 











